        <language>en</language>
        <!--
          To publish a new release, run ./Scripts/release.sh (see RELEASING.md).
          It builds + notarizes + zips the app, signs the zip with the EdDSA
          private key, prepends a new <item> below, and pushes this file. The
          moment the push lands, users on a previous version see an update
          prompt on next launch (or up to 24h later if automatic checks are on).

          Sparkle reads this file via raw.githubusercontent.com, so no GitHub
          Pages or release-asset shuffle is needed.

          DO NOT hand-edit a shipped <item>. Once published, an item's
          version + EdDSA signature pair is part of the trust chain — changing
          it makes existing installs reject the update. Add new items above old
          ones; keep the last few historical entries for users who skip
          versions.

          (No <item> yet: the first Sparkle-enabled release prepends one here.
          The pre-Sparkle purpleirc-v1.0.603 GitHub release is intentionally
          absent — it has no EdDSA signature and predates the updater.)
        -->
